                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13050020" author="julienledem" created="Wed, 15 Jun 2011 21:53:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;attaching &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2128&quot; title=&quot;Generating the jar file takes a lot of time and is unnecessary when running Pig local mode&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-2128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-2128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.patch to skip building the jar when in local mode&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050080" author="dvryaboy" created="Wed, 15 Jun 2011 23:22:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Julien, good idea.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does this work if external jars are registered in the script?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050156" author="dvryaboy" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2011 01:06:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I verified that external jars do work. It&apos;s a significant speedup. +1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please change title of jira to refer to this specific optimization so we don&apos;t have 15 &quot;local mode is slow&quot; tickets as we keep chipping away at this &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050228" author="julienledem" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2011 06:35:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve updated the summary and description&lt;br/&gt;
I am not sure if this could break other things (like register).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050661" author="dvryaboy" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2011 20:16:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I verified that registering jars is fine and properties are picked up (in fact, because we always register fairly sizable jars, this is a significant enough improvement that I already pushed this patch to production in our clusters). So far so good. Go ahead and commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13155630" author="viraj" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2011 02:25:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can this patch be backported to Pig 0.9?&lt;br/&gt;
Viraj&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13155712" author="dvryaboy" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2011 06:22:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Viraj,&lt;br/&gt;
Yes, this patch applies to 0.9 and even 0.8 (possibly with a bit of elbow grease &amp;#8211; I don&apos;t remember now) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Was this a question or a request? &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13161155" author="olgan" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2011 20:58:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We were wondering if this change can be committed to 0.9 branch. It looks pretty benign.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13161305" author="dvryaboy" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2011 23:37:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch applied cleanly, I&apos;m running test-commit right now and will commit assuming it passes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13161313" author="olgan" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2011 23:52:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13161362" author="dvryaboy" created="Fri, 2 Dec 2011 02:03:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed to 0.9.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
